   SANTIAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Copper production in the first-half of 1992 at Codelco, Chile's state-owned
copper corporation, rose to 572,618 tonnes copper, from 564,473 tonnes in
the same period last year, Mr Alejandro Noemi, the chief executive, said at
the weekend, reports Reuter from Santiago. 'First-half fine copper
