FT  27 JUL 92 / Charity shops beat downturn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CHARITY shops are opening at the rate of almost six a week while the
recession drives other stores from the high street, according to Corporate
Intelligence Group, the retail analysts.
In a report it says that shoppers spend Pounds 200m a year in 5,500 charity
shops, which are moving upmarket to attract customers. It adds that it
expects 1,000 further charity shops to open over the next three or four
years.
